==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[widewe]]''
===Noun===
'''widow'''

#<!--NWomanWhoseHusbandDied-->A [[woman]] whose [[husband]] has [[died]] (and has not re-married)
#<!--NWomanWhoseHusbandIsOftenAway-->(''informal, in combination'') A woman whose husband is often away [[pursuing]] a [[sport]] etc
#* A golf-'''widow'''
#<!--NPrinting-->(''printing'') a [[single]] [[line]] of [[type]], that ends a [[paragraph]], carried over to the next [[page]] or [[column]]

